# Privacy Policy for Novel Library

**Last Updated:** February 17, 2026

## Introduction

This Privacy Policy governs the use of Novel Library (the "App"). By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

## Information Collection and Use

### Data We Collect

The App may collect the following types of information:

- **Reading Progress Data**: Novels in your library, chapters read, bookmarks, and reading history
- **App Preferences**: Theme settings, reader configurations, and app settings
- **Device Information**: Device model, operating system version, and app version for crash reporting
- **Firebase Analytics**: Anonymous usage statistics to improve app functionality

### Google Account Integration

- Google account access is used **exclusively** for backup and restore functionality
- We only access the specific backup files created by the App in your Google Drive
- We do not access, read, modify, or collect any other files or data from your Google Drive
- You can revoke this access at any time through your Google Account settings

### Third-Party Content

- The App aggregates content from third-party websites through user-installed extensions
- We do not host, store, or claim ownership of any novel content, text, images, or other materials accessed through the App
- All content belongs to their respective copyright holders

## Data Storage

- Local data is stored on your device
- Cloud backup (optional) is stored in your personal Google Drive account
- We do not maintain servers that store your personal reading data

## Third-Party Services

The App uses the following third-party services:

- **Firebase** (Analytics, Crashlytics, Cloud Messaging, Authentication)
- **Google Drive API** (for backup/restore)
- **Third-party novel source websites** (accessed through extensions)

These services have their own privacy policies governing the use of your information.

